        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 30 at 9:11AM CDT by NWS Houston/Galveston TX</headline>
        <description>At 911 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near East Bernard to 8 miles northwest of
Markham to near Point Comfort. Movement was east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Southern Rosenberg, Bay City, El Campo, Wharton, Edna, Palacios, West
Columbia, Sweeny, South Texas Nuclear Plant, Needville, East Bernard,
Ganado, Pleak, Fairchilds, Beasley, Kendleton, Thompsons, La Ward,
Pierce, and Van Vleck.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
